creator: Karmalicious AB
descriptionHtml:
Karma is the award-winning food app for buying delicious surplus food in London, at half the usual price. Simple and convenient, Karma highlights surplus food in your area to buy, collect and enjoy.

Now with more than 1,600 restaurants, grocery stores, bakeries and cafes to rescue from, and more joining every week.

London: Buy surplus food from Coco di Mama, Black Sheep Coffee, Aubaine, Detox Kitchen and many more.

Eat great food. Save money. Protect the planet.


************************

- Eat great food
Buy delicious unsold surplus food as take away. Order and pay in the app.

- Save money
Find great food deals where you pay half the price and pick up your food as take-away. And you don't have to cook too!

- Save the environment
Help create a more sustainable society by reducing food waste.

***********************

This is how it works:

- Food is uploaded to Karma
Restaurants, grocery stores, bakeries and cafes upload their surplus food at specific times, often between 2pm and 6pm.

- You buy the food
You buy the food you want directly in the Karma app at a lower price.

- You pick up the food
You pick up the food on location as take away. Show your order to the personnel in order to get your food. Enjoy your lunch or dinner!

- Follow your favourite restaurants, cafes and grocery stores to get notified when they have food you can buy. Perhaps you want to know if a restaurant has a meal that you can buy for dinner after work? You'll get a push notification as soon as a place you like has food that you can buy!

title: Karma - Rescue unsold food

creator: Karmalicious AB
descriptionHtml:
We’re slackers. The modern-day climate heroes. The kind of people who help save the world by doing the most basic human thing in life - eat stuff.

We’re running the world’s least ambitious, most delicious climate movement: Radical Slacktivism. To fight over-production and solve food waste.

Join Karma's Slacker Movement. It will feed you.*

*with super discounted food that otherwise would go to waste.

***Now with more than 9,000 connected restaurants, grocery stores, bakeries and cafes in the UK and Sweden to buy take-away food from. The best part? More places join every week!***

************************

- Food on sale. Is this real life?
Yes, you read it. Discounted price on great food.

- It feeds you
All the meals you can think of. Whether you’re hangry, sad, happy or just want to treat yourself.

- Saving the world one slice at a time.
Fight food waste by simply eating.

***********************

Are you still reading? Guess you want to know more huh. Here’s the drill (it’s as easy as 1-2-3).

- Food is uploaded to Karma
Restaurants, grocery stores, bakeries, and cafes upload their surplus food at specific times, often between 2 pm and 6 pm.

- Save food with a tap
You buy the food you want directly in the Karma app at a lower price.

- Take (the easy way) out
Show your order to the personnel to get your food as take away.

************************

Together, we're making sustainability effortless.

************************

Stockholm: Buy food from Vassa Eggen, Nybrogatan 38, Nytorget 6, Grand Central by Scandic, American Table Bar & Brasserie, Gateau, ICA Kvantum Liljeholmen, Freshii, Österlånggatan17, Bröd & Salt, Doctor Salad, Wayne’s Coffee, Panini, PONG and more.

Göteborg: Buy food from Swedish Taste, Le Croissant, The Barn, Francks Kök & Catering, Tiger Deli, Govindas, Lilla Bommen Smörgåsbutik, Cederleüfs & Svenheimers, Kök:17, Bistro Italiano, Muchacho, St. Agnes, Gateau and more.

We’re also live in 200 more cities, such as Malmö, Uppsala, Umeå, Enköping, Norrköping, Borås, Kalmar and Västerås!
